  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\n`assert` and `raise` should only be possible via statements, not callable functions.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nAllowing these two commands to happen as statements _and_ functions creates ambiguity in the syntax without any added benefit that I can see. I believe being opinionated here will make for more readable smart contracts, and means we can reduce some complexity in the vyper codebase.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\n\r\nCurrently all of the following syntax is valid.  This VIP proposes that the second set of examples should be _invalid_.\r\n\r\n```python\r\n# keep this\r\nassert foo, \"oopsie\"\r\nraise \"oopsie\"\r\n\r\n# remove this\r\nassert(foo, \"oopsie\")\r\nraise(\"oopsie\")\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nThis will be a breaking change, if approved we might want to delay it until a major release.\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
